main event: A UFO was sighted near Finland AFS, Minnesota, with visual and radar observations recorded on multiple occasions in September 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed to have blinking lights, changing colors from red to green., A radar confirmation was not attained, but the object was visually tracked for approximately 3 to 4 hours., The sightings involved personnel from both Finley and Finland AFS who reported inconsistent details., One observer described the object as being disc-shaped with green lights, suggesting it was under intelligent control., Another sighting on 7 September also reported a blue, green, and white light that was similarly unexplained.
sighted object: one unidentified flying object with blinking lights
witness description: Airmen at Finland AFS and civilians in the area.
